            <div class="feedback-container" style="display: none;">
                <div class="correct-answer">
                    <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Correct! "Two-way Key" is not a standard cryptography key type. The three main types are symmetric key, asymmetric key, and hash functions.
                </div>
                <div class="incorrect-answer">
                    <i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i> Incorrect. The three main types of cryptography are symmetric key, asymmetric key, and hash functions.
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <button class="simple-button" data-correct="d" onclick="checkAnswer(this, '1-2')">Check My Answer</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

